HEADWORD: Mixtilinear
<hw>Mix`ti*lin"e*ar</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>mixtus</ets> mixed (p.
p. of <ets>miscere</ets> to mix) + E. <ets>lineal</ets>,
<ets>linear</ets>.]</ety> <def>Containing, or consisting of, lines of
different kinds, as straight, curved, and the like; <as>as, a
<ex>mixtilinear</ex> angle, that is, an angle contained by a straight
line and a curve</as>.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mixtion</ent>⟦br⟧
